CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1955, pg. 2, reads: "Eagle Scout - 'Jackie' Butler, 13, of 3030 Iowa Street will be made an Eagle Scout Friday night at a 'Court of Honor,' sponsored by Boy Scout Troop 93, and the Allegheny Council of Boy Scouts of America, Inc., at Grace Memorial Presbyterian Church.  'Jackie' becomes the first Negro Boy Scout in the country to be so honored.  He is shown with Earl Herbert, executive commissioner for the Gateway District of the Boy Scouts. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Eagle Scout Jack Butler from troop 93
